      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my connection at heathrow just got cancelled and im gonna miss my flight to singapore. everything is a mess here. can u help me figure out what i should look for? i need to get there as fast as possible and minimize total travel time. what should my priorities be for finding a new route?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "First, take a deep breath and try to calm down, as panic is the enemy of quick problem-solving. You need to check the airport's official website or app immediately to see your options for rebooking a flight to Singapore, as they often have specific procedures for cancelled connections. Next, look for any available flights to a major hub like London or Dubai where you might catch a direct flight to Singapore, as these are often faster than navigating a complex new itinerary. Finally, prioritize getting to the airport's assistance desk or customer service counter to ask about priority boarding or special transport arrangements, as this can significantly reduce your travel time.\n\nRemember that in these stressful situations, it's easy to lose track of time, so keep your phone charged and your documents handy. You might also want to check if your hotel or accommodation has any resources or recommendations for navigating the airport efficiently. Just like a good strategist, you need to stay focused on the immediate goal of getting to Singapore as quickly as possible, even if the path is messy. You've got this, and with a clear plan, you can handle this situation just fine.",
